(Alina Ukolova via AP)At a Glance The polar bear turned up last week wandering around the village of Tilichiki.
A polar bear that may have floated more than 400 miles on an ice floe to a village in eastern Russia has been returned to its home.
The exhausted-looking animal was seen last week wandering around the village of Tilichiki on Kamchatka.
(MORE: Arctic Russian Town Declares Polar Bear Invasion Emergency After 52 Wander In)Polar bears' dependence on sea ice makes them highly vulnerable to global warming.